{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17614862","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17614862"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T14:49:11+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T14:49:11+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16376"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16376","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16376"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.83,0,0.07,0.03,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9067"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74761"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9067","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9067"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16376"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60247"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"5586"},{"type":"tags","id":"10318"},{"type":"tags","id":"10341"},{"type":"tags","id":"10342"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21555"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21558"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74761","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74761"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following sensory modalities is transmitted via the dorsal column pathway?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Fine touch, vibration, proprioception","Fine touch, temperature","Proprioception only","Temperature only","Fine touch, proprioception"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe dorsal column-medial lemniscal pathway is one of the major ascending sensory pathways in the spinal cord. Understanding which sensations are carried by this pathway is crucial for localising neurological lesions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFine touch, vibration, proprioception\u003C/strong\u003E are all transmitted via the dorsal column pathway. This pathway is responsible for discriminative touch (the ability to localise touch precisely), conscious proprioception (awareness of limb position), and vibration sense. These modalities require precise spatial and temporal information to reach the cortex.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFine touch, temperature\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because temperature sensation travels via the spinothalamic tract, along with pain and crude touch sensation. The spinothalamic tract crosses to the opposite side of the spinal cord shortly after entering.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProprioception only\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because while proprioception does travel via the dorsal columns, it is not the only sensation that uses this pathway.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETemperature only\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because temperature sensation travels via the spinothalamic tract, not the dorsal columns.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFine touch, proprioception\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because while these sensations do travel via the dorsal columns, vibration sense also uses this pathway.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn clinical practice, testing these different sensory modalities helps localise lesions. For example, a dorsal column lesion would affect vibration sense, proprioception, and fine touch while preserving temperature sensation, as seen in conditions like subacute combined degeneration of the cord.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The dorsal column-medial lemniscal pathway transmits fine touch, vibration and proprioception but not temperature sensation.","Temperature sensation is transmitted via the spinothalamic tract along with pain and crude touch.","The dorsal column pathway is important for discriminative touch and conscious proprioception needed for skilled movements."],"references":["Al-Chalabi M, Reddy V, Alsalman I. Neuroanatomy, Posterior Column (Dorsal Column) [Updated 2023 Apr 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK507888/","Singh, V. (2024).\u00a0Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022).\u00a0The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60247"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16376"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60247","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60247"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-26T21:55:03+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-26T23:00:06+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9067"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74761"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"headin